Step-by-step calculation:

1. Gross Profit Margin  
   Formula: Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
   From the income statement:  
   • Gross Profit = 2,060,619.40  
   • Total Revenue = 3,397,619.40  
   Calculation:  
   Gross Profit Margin = (2,060,619.40 / 3,397,619.40) × 100 ≈ 60.64%

2. Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
   Formula: Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities  
   From the cash flow statement and balance sheet:  
   • Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -1,368,775.90  
   • Total Current Liabilities = 631,880.98  
   Calculation:  
   Operating Cash Flow Ratio = -1,368,775.90 / 631,880.98 ≈ -2.17

Thus, the final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "60.64%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-2.17"
  }
}
